<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 03 at 6:01PM CDT  by NWS Midland-Odessa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Crane
and southern Upton Counties through 645 PM CDT...
At 600 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Crane, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Crane, Rankin and King Mountain.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
